<doc id="223374" wikidata="Q2607656" url="?curid=223374" title="Tor (fish)">
<text>Tor is a genus of freshwater ray-finned fishes belonging to the family Cyprinidae, the family which includes the carps, barbs and related fishes. The fishes in this genus, and some related genera, are commonly known as mahseers. These fishes are found in Asia.

==Species==
The currently recognized species in this genus are:
* &quot;Tor ater&quot; 
* &quot;Tor barakae&quot; 
* &quot;Tor dongnaiensis&quot; (Dongnai mahseer)
* &quot;Tor khudree&quot; (Black mahseer)
* &quot;Tor kulkarnii&quot; (Dwarf mahseer)
* &quot;Tor laterivittatus&quot; 
* &quot;Tor mahanadicus&quot; 
* &quot;Tor malabaricus&quot; (Malabar mahseer)
* &quot;Tor mekongensis&quot; 
* &quot;Tor mosal&quot; 
* &quot;Tor polylepis&quot; 
* &quot;Tor putitora&quot; (Himalayan mahseer)
* &quot;Tor remadevii&quot; (Orange-finned mahseer)
* &quot;Tor sinensis&quot; (Chinese mahseer)
* &quot;Tor tambra&quot; 
* &quot;Tor tambroides&quot; (Malayan mahseer, empurau)
* &quot;Tor tor&quot; (Red-finned mahseer)
* &quot;Tor yingjiangensis&quot; (Yingjiang mahseer)

